<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4675322>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 4. Pseudochalaraspidum hanseni [SIO 56-76]. (A) Posterior end of the labrum (posterior is up), ventral view. Armature of the ‘hook’. (B) Distal segment of the right mandibular palp with row of fine feathered setae of equal length on the ventral margin and some additional setae on the inner surface. (C) Left mandible, view on the edge with incisor process (ip), lacinia mobilis (lm), cusp c (cc) and the reduced molar process (mp). (D) Left mandible, posterior view. (E) Right mandible, view on the edge. (F) Right mandible, anterior view. Between incisor and molar process, cusps b (cb) and c (cc). The notch between the two cusps (arrow) is indistinct. (G) Paragnaths, anterior view, ventral is up. The left paragnath (lp) is sculptured, the right paragnath (rp) of more ‘normal’ shape. (H) Left paragnath, ventral view, anterior is up; maxillula (mx 1) posterior of paragnath." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4675322/files/figure.png" .

