<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4675320>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. Chalaraspidum alatum [SIO 60-243]. (A) Maxillula, posterior view, with paragnaths (pg) in the background. Notice the single seta on the surface of the outer endite (oe). (B) Magnification of the strong cuspidate setae of the outer endites. (C) Left Maxilla, ventral (posterior) view. The two-segmented palp (p) is located between exopod (ex) and the two endites (en1, en2). (D) Right maxilliped, ventral (posterior) view. The protopod (pp) consisting of the fused coxa and basis carries the five-segmented endopod (ep) and the exopod (ex). The epipodite is removed." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4675320/files/figure.png" .

