<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4675316>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 1. Lophogaster subglaber. (A) Left part of the mouthparts shown from the median food channel. Anterior is left, ventral is up. The morphological correlation between mandible (with lacinia mobilis, lm) and paragnath (pg) can be seen. The strong endopod of the maxilliped (mxp) covers the maxillula with outer (oe) and inner endite. The maxilla cannot be seen. (B) Right part of the mouthparts shown from the median food channel. Anterior is right, ventral is up. The mandible is located between labrum (lbr) and paragnath (pg). The hook of the labrum tooth (lt) is orientated medially. The molar process of the mandible is close to the oesophagus (oe). A few longer setae of the inner endite (ie) of the maxillula reach into the food channel." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4675316/files/figure.png" .

