<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4675324>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 5. Pseudochalaraspidum hanseni. (A) Maxillula [SIO 56-76], posterior view, with paragnaths (pg) in the background. On the surface of the outer endite (oe) a single seta is present. (B) Magnification of the strong cuspidate setae of the outer endites. (C) Right Maxilla [SIO 56-76], ventral (posterior) view. Between exopod (ex) and the two endites (en1, en2) the one-segmented palp (p). (D) Left maxilliped [USNM 82422], ventral (posterior) view. The protopod (pp) consisting of the fused coxa and basis carries the five-segmented endopod (ep) and the exopod (ex). The epipodite is removed." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4675324/files/figure.png" .

